user_story: I am a Dutch openfiber customer and want to do online banking on my Interbank account in the US and I want to be sure my bank is not being spoofed and that my route is not hijacked and I heard that Brazil often tries to intercept bank traffic so I want to exclude Brazil

I am a researcher at Yukon university in Canada and I want to set up a network research project with Cornell university in the US to do some network research and i want to be able to call any of my hops to find out what happens if problems occur and the traffic should not go to any country but US and Canada

I am an exotic tourist in Bhutan (Asia) using the SuperNet Infocomm network and I want to send some pictures back to my family in Brazil which use the Infolic Telecom network while making sure the pictures take the correct path so that I don't have to send them again which is very expensive here in the rural area where I am
I am an APNIC employee and I want to secretly watch some American sports from Comcast but nobody may notice so I want the very best connection possible

I am a Russian content creator using the Foton Telecom network wanting to upload some video material to my cloud environment at Datacenter One GmbH in Germany and I want a safe route with no route hijacking and I don't want US people to intercept my traffic
